So if I try to call a method without an impl block, it won’t compile? 
```rust
let s = MyStruct;
s.meth();
```

I tried this:
```rust
struct Point { x:i32, y:i32 }
impl Point {
    fn translate(self: &Self, dx:i32) -> Self { Self{x+dx, y} }
}
```
But I’m trying to implement a builder pattern using an `impl` block and it’s not working.

No worries! A struct just groups data, and an impl block puts methods or associated functions. Here’s a quick example:
struct Config { host: String port: u16 }
impl Config {
    pub fn new(host: &str port: u16) -> Self { Self{host port} }
    pub fn set_port(&mut self p: u16) { self.port = p; } }
